An Australian man convicted of the notorious 'body in the bath' murder of his fiancee has been freed on bail after spending 20 years behind bars.

Henry Victor Keogh, 57, was jailed for a minimum of 25 years when he was convicted of murdering his fiancee Anna-Jane Cheney, then 29, in their bath in March 1994.

In a landmark legal decision, Mr Keogh was granted a retrial after an appeal brought before Adelaide Supreme Court on Monday. 

